# GitHub Workflow Guardrails

- Never push directly to `main`. It is branch-protected and requires pull requests.
- Create a feature branch for all work, then open/update a PR early.
- Assume required checks must pass before merge; do not treat local success as enough.
- Before declaring work done, run project checks that match changed areas (at minimum `ruff` + relevant `pytest` suites).
- If workflow files change, run `actionlint` locally when available, and always verify the Actionlint CI check.
- For release tags, verify generated artifacts and signatures (`gh attestation verify`, `cosign verify-blob`) before finalizing.
- Use `gh run list` / `gh run view` to confirm CI status instead of assuming green.

## Quick Commands

```bash
git status -sb
gh pr view --json url,state,headRefName,baseRefName
gh run list --limit 10
```
